 {'from': 'human', 'value': "I'll try to consider it, Alex. But sometimes, I feel so hopeless. I've let addiction consume so much of my life that I don't know if I can ever truly recover. The thought of failing again terrifies me, and it adds another layer of pressure and expectations."}
 {'from': 'gpt', 'value': "Charlie, it's important to remember that recovery is a process, and setbacks happen to many people. You've already taken the first step by recognizing the impact addiction has had on your life. It's okay to feel scared and unsure, but it's also vital to believe in your ability to heal and make positive changes."}
